            <title>[SOLR-16467] Upgrade semver4j to 2.2.0 to fix failures with some locales</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16467</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15910&quot; title=&quot;Upgrade semver library to fix versioning constraint bugs in the PackageManager&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15910&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15910&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; upgrades the semver library and Solr tests found that semver4j has issues with some Locales. I don&apos;t see an easy way to address this in Solr - so fixing upstream: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/semver4j/semver4j/pull/85&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/semver4j/semver4j/pull/85&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once fixed upstream this should be a simple library upgrade. In the meantime I will annotate the test awaits fix or limit the locales.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
